Mother Jones found the yearly cost of gun violence in the US is $229 billion per person . 
  The figure is more than Apple's annual revenue of $174 billion and the cost of the obesity epidemic is $224 billion . 
  Investigation was prompted by the 2012 shooting in Aurora, Colorado . 
  At least 750,000 people were injured by guns in 2012 . 
  The yearly cost to send someone to prison for gun-related homicide is $414,000 . 
 